<p>I'm working on a submission form for events that once completed, goes to a processing page and updates a database.</p>  <p>I have fourteen fields, several are required one of which is the date and time of the event.</p>  <p>During the processing of the form I join the two form entries, date and time before attempting the insert into the database but an error occurs.</p>  <blockquote>   <p>Data truncation: Incorrect datetime value</p> </blockquote>  <p>Here is the code elements that are failing:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;cfset insdate = form["date"] &amp; form["time"]&gt; &lt;cfset new_date = #CREATEODBCDATETIME(insdate)#&gt;  &lt;cfif len(trim("#institle#"))&gt;         &lt;cfquery name="modify"&gt;             INSERT INTO table             SET             title = &lt;cfqueryparam                                            cfsqltype="CF_SQL_LONGVARCHAR"                       value="#institle#"&gt;,             dateTime = &lt;cfqueryparam                       cfsqltype="CF_SQL_LONGVARCHAR"                       value="#new_date#"&gt;,             location = &lt;cfqueryparam                       cfsqltype="CF_SQL_LONGVARCHAR"                       value="#inslocation#"&gt;,             category = &lt;cfqueryparam                       cfsqltype="CF_SQL_SMALLINT"                       value="#inscategory#"&gt;,             type = &lt;cfqueryparam                       cfsqltype="CF_SQL_TINYINT"                       value="#instype#"&gt;                                             &lt;/cfquery&gt; &lt;/cfif&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I've trimmed the code above to make it shorter and easier to read. If anyone has any ideas what I'm doing wrong, that would be great.</p>  <p>I'm running Coldfusion 8, a mySQL database and the database accepts datetime on the field in question, in a yyyy-mm-dd hh:mm:ss format.</p>  <p>Cheers.</p>